<item>
            <title>[AMQ-6063] NullPointerException during KahaDB index recovery</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-6063</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;A broker I was testing ran out of disk space the other day when messages were being written to it because disk usage checks were not set.  After restart, the KahaDB index was detected as corrupted but during the recovery a NullPointerException occurred.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The error occurred in MessageDatabase inside recoveryIndex on this line:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;sd.locationIndex.remove(tx.keys.location)&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
